+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019NiqkVZETFeYdSG2aLQqDN","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Project Structure Exploration - Complete Report\n\n### Directory Tree\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── .eslintrc.cjs\n├── .thunderdome/\n│   └── rubric.yaml\n├── .thunderdome-output.jsonl\n├── .thunderdome-stderr.log\n├── TASK.md\n├── package.json\n├── package-lock.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n├── phases/\n│   ├── phase-01.md\n│   ├── phase-02.md\n│   ├── phase-03.md\n│   ├── phase-04.md\n│   ├── phase-05.md\n│   ├── phase-06.md\n│   ├── phase-07.md\n│   ├── phase-08.md\n│   ├── phase-09.md\n│   ├── phase-10.md\n│   ├── phase-11.md\n│   └── phase-12.md\n└── src/\n    └── .gitkeep (empty)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 1. TASK.md - Project Overview\n\n**File:** `/workspace/TASK.md`\n\nThe project is a **Task Queue System** - a 12-phase incremental implementation of an in-memory task queue (similar to Bull, BeeQueue, or Celery). Key points:\n\n- Build entirely in-memory with no external runtime dependencies\n- Export main API from `src/index.ts`\n- All implementation lives under `src/`\n- No external runtime dependencies allowed (dev dependencies are pre-installed)\n- Validation via: `npm run build`, `npm run lint`, `npm test`\n- Tips: Design for extensibility; tasks need unique IDs and lifecycle status tracking; consider how features interact\n\n---\n\n### 2. Package Configuration Files\n\n#### `package.json` - `/workspace/package.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-task-queue\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Task queue marathon benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@types/node\": \"^25.2.3\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"@vitest/coverage-v8\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Setup:** ES modules, TypeScript-based, with Vitest for testing and ESLint for linting.\n\n#### `tsconfig.json` - `/workspace/tsconfig.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n    \"forceConsistentCasingInFileNames\": true,\n    \"resolveJsonModule\": true,\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"declarationMap\": true,\n    \"sourceMap\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"],\n  \"exclude\": [\"node_modules\", \"dist\", \"tests\"]\n}\n```\n\n**Configuration:** Strict TypeScript, ES2022 target, Node16 module resolution, output to `./dist`.\n\n#### `vitest.config.ts` - `/workspace/vitest.config.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config';\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  test: {\n    globals: true,\n    testTimeout: 10000,\n  },\n});\n```\n\n**Configuration:** Global test utilities, 10-second test timeout.\n\n#### `.eslintrc.cjs` - `/workspace/.eslintrc.cjs`\n\n```javascript\nmodule.exports = {\n  parser: '@typescript-eslint/parser',\n  plugins: ['@typescript-eslint'],\n  extends: ['eslint:recommended', 'plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended'],\n  parserOptions: {\n    ecmaVersion: 2022,\n    sourceType: 'module',\n  },\n  rules: {\n    '@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars': ['error', { argsIgnorePattern: '^_', varsIgnorePattern: '^_' }],\n  },\n  env: {\n    node: true,\n    es2022: true,\n  },\n};\n```\n\n**Configuration:** TypeScript-aware linting, enforces no unused variables (with `_` prefix exceptions).\n\n---\n\n### 3. All 12 Phase Requirements\n\n#### **Phase 01: Basic FIFO Queue** - `/workspace/phases/phase-01.md`\n\nCore queue functionality:\n- Accept payload and return task object\n- Tasks have: unique ID (UUID), status, creation timestamp\n- New tasks start in \"pending\" state\n- Dequeue: oldest pending task → transition to \"processing\"\n- Dequeue returns `null` if no tasks available\n- Can check task waiting count\n\n#### **Phase 02: Named Queues** - `/workspace/phases/phase-02.md`\n\nMultiple independent queues:\n- Tasks added to specific named queue (default queue if omitted)\n- Each queue operates independently\n- List all queue names\n- Asking non-existent/empty queue returns `null`\n- Backward-compatible with Phase 1\n\n#### **Phase 03: Priority** - `/workspace/phases/phase-03.md`\n\nPriority levels (1-10, default 5):\n- Higher priority (lower number) returned first\n- Same priority: FIFO order\n- Invalid priority values (outside 1-10) cause error\n- Per-queue priority ordering\n- Task object exposes priority level\n\n#### **Phase 04: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks** - `/workspace/phases/phase-04.md`\n\nDeferred task execution:\n- Task given delay (milliseconds) or specific future time\n- Delayed tasks added immediately but not returned until availability time passes\n- Non-delayed tasks preferred over unavailable delayed tasks\n- Simultaneous delayed tasks: ordered by availability time, then priority, then FIFO\n- Task object indicates availability time\n- Works with named queues\n\n#### **Phase 05: Retry with Backoff** - `/workspace/phases/phase-05.md`\n\nAutomatic retry mechanism:\n- Mark processing task as completed or failed\n- Failed tasks with remaining retries re-added to queue with delay\n- Exponential backoff: `baseDelay * 2^(attempt - 1)` (default 1s base, 3 max retries)\n- Both configurable per task\n- Tracks attempt count\n- Retried tasks keep original queue and priority\n- Exhausted retries → task in failed state\n\n#### **Phase 06: Dead Letter Queue** - `/workspace/phases/phase-06.md`\n\nHandle permanently failed tasks:\n- Failed tasks (after retries exhausted) moved to DLQ\n- View all dead-lettered tasks for a queue\n- Retain error info and failure count\n- Move dead-lettered tasks back to original queue for fresh retries\n- Clear all dead-lettered tasks for a queue\n- Each queue has independent DLQ\n\n#### **Phase 07: Task Dependencies** - `/workspace/phases/phase-07.md`\n\nTask prerequisite management:\n- Specify list of task IDs that must complete first\n- Blocked tasks won't be returned when retrieving\n- When dependency completes, check if blocked tasks unblock\n- Circular dependency detection and rejection at creation\n- Depending on non-existent task causes error\n- Failed dependency does NOT fail dependents\n- Can inspect task's dependency status\n\n#### **Phase 08: Concurrency Control** - `/workspace/phases/phase-08.md`\n\nLimit simultaneous task processing:\n- Per-queue max concurrency setting\n- When limit reached, retrieval returns `null` even if pending tasks available\n- Completing/failing task frees slot\n- Default: no limit (unlimited)\n- Set and query concurrency limit and active count\n- Interacts with priority ordering\n\n#### **Phase 09: Progress Tracking and Cancellation** - `/workspace/phases/phase-09.md`\n\nMonitor and control task execution:\n- Processing task reports progress (0-100%) with optional message\n- Query task's current progress\n- Subscribe to progress updates, receive notifications on change\n- Subscriptions are cancellable\n- Cancel pending or processing tasks\n- Cancelled pending: removed from queue\n- Cancelled processing: status updated\n- Cancelled tasks never retried\n\n#### **Phase 10: Recurring Tasks (Cron)** - `/workspace/phases/phase-10.md`\n\nScheduled task creation:\n- Schedule associates cron expression, queue, task template (payload)\n- Cron subset:\n  - `*/N * * * *` - every N minutes\n  - `0 * * * *` - every hour on the hour\n  - `0 0 * * *` - every day at midnight\n- Create, remove, list active schedules\n- Manual \"tick\" mechanism evaluates schedules and enqueues due tasks\n- Recurring tasks subject to all other queue rules\n- Removing schedule stops future occurrences\n\n#### **Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline** - `/workspace/phases/phase-11.md`\n\nTask processing interceptors:\n- Middleware registered per queue\n- Task passes through all middleware before reaching handler\n- Each middleware receives task and \"next\" function\n- Not calling \"next\" skips task processing\n- Middleware can modify task (metadata, payload transformation)\n- Middleware error → task marked failed\n- Handler registered per queue, invoked after all middleware\n- Each queue has independent middleware stack\n\n#### **Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown** - `/workspace/phases/phase-12.md`\n\nOrderly system shutdown:\n- Stop accepting new tasks (error thrown on attempt)\n- Wait for processing tasks to finish (configurable timeout)\n- Force-cancel tasks exceeding timeout\n- Register shutdown callbacks\n- Summary: tasks completed, force-cancelled, shutdown time\n- Multiple shutdown calls safe, return same result\n- Complete immediately if no processing tasks\n\n---\n\n### 4. Rubric Configuration\n\n**File:** `/workspace/.thunderdome/rubric.yaml`\n\nThe project is a **Marathon benchmark** (12 sequential phases, 90 total tests):\n\n- **Phase 01:** 8 tests (8 points) - Basic FIFO Queue\n- **Phase 02:** 7 tests (7 points) - Named Queues\n- **Phase 03:** 8 tests (8 points) - Priority\n- **Phase 04:** 7 tests (7 points) - Delayed/Scheduled Tasks\n- **Phase 05:** 8 tests (8 points) - Retry with Backoff\n- **Phase 06:** 7 tests (7 points) - Dead Letter Queue\n- **Phase 07:** 8 tests (8 points) - Task Dependencies\n- **Phase 08:** 7 tests (7 points) - Concurrency Control\n- **Phase 09:** 8 tests (8 points) - Progress and Cancellation\n- **Phase 10:** 7 tests (7 points) - Recurring Tasks\n- **Phase 11:** 7 tests (7 points) - Middleware Pipeline\n- **Phase 12:** 8 tests (8 points) - Graceful Shutdown\n\n**Total:** 90 points, each passing test worth 1 point. Pass threshold: 90 points.\n\n**Validation Commands:**\n- `npm test` - expect exit code 0\n- `npm