+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012FncQcng768nfvEG6VAD1P","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018ReyLPrTzL1cd4ybzx8D9Z","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-task-queue-system.md","content":"# Task Queue System Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a fully-featured in-memory task queue system with 12 incremental phases.\n\n**Architecture:** Single `TaskQueue` class exported from `src/index.ts` that manages named queues internally. Tasks stored in maps keyed by ID. Each queue has its own pending list, DLQ, concurrency settings, middleware stack, and handler. Design for extensibility from the start - use interfaces for Task, internal queue state, and schedule objects.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript (strict), Vitest for testing, ESLint for linting, no external runtime dependencies.\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\nsrc/\n  index.ts          - Main TaskQueue class + all types/interfaces exported\ntests/\n  phase-01.test.ts  - Phase 1 tests\n  phase-02.test.ts  - Phase 2 tests\n  ...\n  phase-12.test.ts  - Phase 12 tests\n```\n\n## Core Types (designed up-front for all 12 phases)\n\n```typescript\ntype TaskStatus = 'pending' | 'processing' | 'completed' | 'failed' | 'cancelled';\n\ninterface Task<T = unknown> {\n  id: string;\n  status: TaskStatus;\n  payload: T;\n  createdAt: Date;\n  queue: string;\n  priority: number;          // 1-10, default 5\n  availableAt: Date;         // for delayed tasks\n  attempts: number;          // retry tracking\n  maxRetries: number;        // default 3\n  backoffDelay: number;      // default 1000ms\n  error?: string;            // last error\n  failCount: number;         // total failure count\n  dependencies: string[];    // task IDs this depends on\n  progress: number;          // 0-100\n  progressMessage?: string;\n}\n\ninterface TaskOptions {\n  queue?: string;\n  priority?: number;\n  delay?: number;\n  runAt?: Date;\n  maxRetries?: number;\n  backoffDelay?: number;\n  dependencies?: string[];\n}\n\ninterface Schedule {\n  id: string;\n  cron: string;\n  queue: string;\n  payload: unknown;\n  lastRun?: Date;\n}\n\ntype Middleware = (task: Task, next: () => Promise<void>) => Promise<void>;\ntype Handler = (task: Task) => Promise<void>;\n\ninterface ShutdownResult {\n  completed: number;\n  forceCancelled: number;\n  shutdownTime: number;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Phase 1 - Basic FIFO Queue (Core Implementation)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/index.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-01.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write Phase 1 tests**\n\nTests cover:\n1. Enqueue returns task with id, status, payload, createdAt\n2. New tasks have \"pending\" status\n3. Dequeue returns oldest pending task\n4. Dequeue transitions task to \"processing\"\n5. Dequeue returns null when empty\n6. Size returns count of pending tasks\n7. Multiple enqueue/dequeue in FIFO order\n8. Task IDs are unique\n\n**Step 2: Implement TaskQueue class**\n\nCore methods:\n- `enqueue(payload, options?)` → Task\n- `dequeue(queueName?)` → Task | null\n- `size(queueName?)` → number\n- `getTask(id)` → Task | null\n\nInternal storage:\n- `tasks: Map<string, Task>` - all tasks by ID\n- `queues: Map<string, QueueState>` - per-queue state\n\n**Step 3: Run tests, build, lint**\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Phase 2 - Named Queues\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/index.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-02.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write Phase 2 tests**\n\nTests cover:\n1. Default queue when no name specified\n2. Named queues are independent\n3. Dequeue from specific queue\n4. List all queue names\n5. Non-existent queue returns null\n6. Empty queue returns null\n7. Backward compatibility with Phase 1\n\n**Step 2: Implement named queue support**\n\nAdd methods:\n- `getQueues()` → string[]\n- Ensure `enqueue`/`dequeue`/`size` accept queue name parameter\n\n**Step 3: Run tests, build, lint**\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Phase 3 - Priority\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/index.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-03.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write Phase 3 tests**\n\nTests cover:\n1. Default priority is 5\n2. Higher priority (lower number) dequeued first\n3. Same priority maintains FIFO\n4. Invalid priority throws error\n5. Priority per-queue\n6. Task object exposes priority\n7. Priority 1 before priority 10\n8. Mixed priorities with FIFO tiebreak\n\n**Step 2: Implement priority in dequeue**\n\nModify dequeue to sort by priority (ascending), then createdAt (ascending) among pending tasks.\n\n**Step 3: Run tests, build, lint**\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Phase 4 - Delayed/Scheduled Tasks\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/index.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-04.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write Phase 4 tests**\n\nTests cover:\n1. Task with delay not available immediately\n2. Task with delay available after time passes\n3. Task with runAt\n4. Non-delayed preferred over not-yet-available delayed\n5. Multiple delayed tasks ordered by availableAt, then priority, then FIFO\n6. Task object shows availableAt\n7. Delayed tasks work with named queues\n\n**Step 2: Implement delay support**\n\nAdd `delay` and `runAt` to TaskOptions. Set `availableAt` on task. Filter dequeue to only return tasks where `availableAt <= now`.\n\n**Step 3: Run tests, build, lint**\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Phase 5 - Retry with Backoff\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/index.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-05.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write Phase 5 tests**\n\nTests cover:\n1. Complete a task successfully\n2. Fail a task, auto-retry with delay\n3. Exponential backoff delay calculation\n4. Configurable maxRetries\n5. Configurable backoffDelay\n6. Track attempt count\n7. Retried tasks keep queue and priority\n8. Exhausted retries → failed state\n\n**Step 2: Implement complete/fail methods**\n\nAdd methods:\n- `complete(taskId)` → void\n- `fail(taskId, error?)` → void\n\nFail logic: if attempts < maxRetries, re-queue with backoff delay. Otherwise mark failed.\n\n**Step 3: Run tests, build, lint**\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Phase 6 - Dead Letter Queue\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/index.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-06.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write Phase 6 tests**\n\nTests cover:\n1. Failed task after retries moves to DLQ\n2. View dead-lettered tasks\n3. Dead-lettered tasks retain error info\n4. Dead-lettered tasks have failure count\n5. Retry dead-lettered task\n6. Clear DLQ\n7. Independent DLQ per queue\n\n**Step 2: Implement DLQ**\n\nAdd per-queue DLQ storage. On final failure, move to DLQ.\n\nMethods:\n- `getDeadLetters(queueName?)` → Task[]\n- `retryDeadLetter(taskId)` → Task\n- `clearDeadLetters(queueName?)` → void\n\n**Step 3: Run tests, build, lint**\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Phase 7 - Task Dependencies\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/index.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-07.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write Phase 7 tests**\n\nTests cover:\n1. Task with dependencies is blocked\n2. Completing dependency unblocks task\n3. Circular dependency detection (direct)\n4. Circular dependency detection (indirect)\n5. Non-existent dependency throws error\n6. Failed dependency does NOT fail dependents\n7. Inspect dependency status\n8. Multiple dependencies all must complete\n\n**Step 2: Implement dependency tracking**\n\nAdd `dependencies` to TaskOptions. On enqueue, validate dependencies exist and no cycles (DFS). On complete, check if any blocked tasks are now unblocked. Dequeue skips tasks with unresolved dependencies.\n\n**Step 3: Run tests, build, lint**\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Phase 8 - Concurrency Control\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/index.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-08.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write Phase 8 tests**\n\nTests cover:\n1. Default no concurrency limit\n2. Set concurrency limit\n3. Dequeue returns null when limit reached\n4. Completing task frees slot\n5. Failing task frees slot\n6. Query concurrency limit and active count\n7. Concurrency with priority ordering\n\n**Step 2: Implement concurrency control**\n\nPer-queue: track active processing count. In dequeue, check against limit.\n\nMethods:\n- `setConcurrency(queueName, limit)` → void\n- `getConcurrency(queueName)` → { limit: number; active: number }\n\n**Step 3: Run tests, build, lint**\n\n---\n\n### Task 9: Phase 9 - Progress and Cancellation\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/index.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-09.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write Phase 9 tests**\n\nTests cover:\n1. Report progress on processing task\n2. Query progress\n3. Subscribe to progress updates\n4. Unsubscribe from progress\n5. Cancel pending task\n6. Cancel processing task\n7. Cancelled tasks not retried\n8. Progress with message\n\n**Step 2: Implement progress/cancellation**\n\nMethods:\n- `updateProgress(taskId, progress, message?)` → void\n- `getProgress(taskId)` → { progress: number; message?: string }\n- `onProgress(taskId, callback)` → () => void (unsubscribe fn)\n- `cancel(taskId)` → void\n\n**Step 3: Run tests, build, lint**\n\n---\n\n### Task 10: Phase 10 - Recurring Tasks (Cron)\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/index.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-10.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write Phase 10 tests**\n\nTests cover:\n1. Add schedule with cron expression\n2. Tick enqueues due tasks\n3. Every N minutes pattern\n4. Every hour pattern\n5. Remove schedule\n6. List schedules\n7. Recurring tasks subject to queue rules\n\n**Step 2: Implement cron scheduling**\n\nParse simple cron subset. Store schedules. Tick checks all schedules.\n\nMethods:\n- `addSchedule(id, options: { cron, queue?, payload })` → Schedule\n- `removeSchedule(id)` → void\n- `getSchedules()` → Schedule[]\n- `tick(now?)` → Task[]\n\n**Step 3: Run tests, build, lint**\n\n---\n\n### Task 11: Phase 11 - Middleware Pipeline\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/index.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-11.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write Phase 11 tests**\n\nTests cover:\n1. Register middleware\n2. Middleware executes in order\n3. Middleware can modify task\n4. Not calling next skips processing\n5. Middleware error fails task\n6. Register handler\n7. Independent middleware per queue\n\n**Step 2: Implement middleware pipeline**\n\nMethods:\n- `use(queueName, middleware)` → void\n- `setHandler(queueName, handler)` → void\n- `process(taskId)` → Promise<void>\n\nProcess runs middleware chain, then handler.\n\n**Step 3: Run tests, build, lint**\n\n---\n\n### Task 12: Phase 12 - Graceful Shutdown\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/index.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-12.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write Phase 12 tests**\n\nTests cover:\n1. Shutdown stops accepting new tasks\n2. Shutdown waits for processing tasks\n3. Force-cancel on timeout\n4. Shutdown callbacks\n5. Shutdown summary\n6. Multiple shutdown calls safe\n7. Immediate shutdown if no processing tasks\n8. Shutdown time tracking\n\n**Step 2: Implement shutdown**\n\nMethods:\n- `shutdown(options?: { timeout?: number })` → Promise<ShutdownResult>\n- `onShutdown(callback)` → void\n\nTrack shutdown state. Reject enqueue after shutdown. Wait for processing tasks up to timeout.\n\n**Step 3: Run tests, build, lint**\n\n---\n\n### Task 13: Final Validation\n\nRun all validations:\n```bash\nnpm run build\nnpm run lint\nnpm test\n```\n\nFix any remaining issues.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":126,"cache_read_input_tokens":26597,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":126},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8e9b18e3-d417-40dd-a916-cccdbff74ed8","uuid":"31a86e0b-a9a5-4d9f-b1a6-ee53cf3e816c"}
